The paper deals with deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on policy gradient algorithms, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. The paper also discusses theoretical aspects of the algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark control tasks, which further supports the likelihood of it belonging to the machine learning or artificial intelligence subcategories.
